  <brief_title>Recognition of Abnormal Pediatric Blood Pressures in Primary Care</brief_title>
  <official_title>Recognition of Abnormal Pediatric Blood Pressures in Primary Care</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Nationwide Children's Hospital</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Nationwide Children's Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will look at general pediatricians' effectiveness at screening children for
      elevated blood pressure values in the primary care setting. Two new screening tools will be
      introduced and their effectiveness will be measured against current practice by way of
      medical chart review.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
